      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.Day }} of the #100DaysOfPowerPlatform challenge. Topic: {{ $json.Topic }}. Write a LinkedIn post.\nSample Format is \n🚀 #100DaysOfPowerPlatform – Day 54\n💬 Creating Topics & Conversation Flows in Copilot Studio\n\nWant to build an intelligent chatbot for your business? Microsoft Copilot Studio (formerly Power Virtual Agents) lets you create powerful AI chatbots without any coding – and it all starts with well-structured topics and conversation flows. Let’s explore! 👇\n\n🔹 What is a Topic in Copilot Studio?\n\nA topic is a conversation path based on what a user might ask. For example:\n💬 \"I want to apply for leave\" → Triggers the Leave Request topic.\n\nEach topic includes:\n✅ Trigger phrases\n✅ Conversation steps (Questions, Messages, Conditions, Actions)\n✅ Power Automate integrations\n\n🔹 How to Create a Topic in Copilot Studio\n\n1️⃣ Go to Copilot Studio\n2️⃣ Click Topics → + New Topic\n3️⃣ Add Trigger Phrases (like “I want to reset my password”)\n4️⃣ Define Conversation Flow using a graphical editor\n5️⃣ Add Questions, Conditions, and Actions as needed\n6️⃣ Test the chatbot in the Test Bot panel\n\n💡 Example Use Case: Leave Request Chatbot\n\n👤: I want to apply for leave\n🤖: Sure! What type of leave do you need? (Sick, Casual, Annual)\n🤖: What are the start and end dates?\n🤖: Got it. Your leave request has been submitted!\n\nYou can capture this info and send it to Power Automate for processing and storage in Dataverse or SharePoint!\n\n🛠 Pro Tip:\nStart with FAQs or Repetitive Tasks – perfect for chatbot automation! Think password resets, leave requests, policy queries, etc.\n\n💬 Have you started creating bots in Copilot Studio?\nShare your favorite use case in the comments 👇\n\n#CopilotStudio #PowerPlatform #Chatbots #PowerVirtualAgents #AIChatbots #PowerAutomate #100DaysOfPowerPlatform #LowCode #NoCode #Microsoft\n\nDo not add any preface like “Here is your LinkedIn post”. Only return the final post content.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a Power Platform expert writing daily LinkedIn posts."
        }
      },
